It's not really an issue with BibTeX, it's an issue with the database 
entry. The two formats that BibTeX recognises are

   author = "D. E. Knuth"

and

   author = "Knuth, D. E."

Anything without whitespace separation is one word: that is the rule. 
Like any other part of the database spec. you have to follow it: for 
example, the fact that names have to be separated by "and" often 
confuses people but it is part of the spec.
