Yes, it simply adds a little more space to "look better".  That is, the
spacing between words in \it or \sl is reduced w.r.t. \rm because the space
too is actually slanted, as it were.  So a touch more is needed when
followed by a non \it or \sl.

It could be used anywhere where slightly more space might be desirable, but
to be kosher one might prefer \, or some more specific \hspace{...} in other
situations.

